<h2 class="contentheading">
	Joomla Daily Message Module Tutorial</h2>



<p class="buttonheading">
	</p>






One of the simplest ways of integrating an
existing program into a new Joomla installation is through the
construction of a module. If you are unsure of whether to build a
component or a module, read <a href="/articles/11?task=view">The Difference Between Components and Modules</a>. Modules are typically well suited for smaller features (news headlines, polls, etc...) to complement the main body of content.<br /><br />This tutorial is an extension of the <a href="/tutorials/9?task=view" class="ext">Daily Message Component Tutorial</a>.
To use this module successfully, it is necessary to install the Daily
Message component. Although this module is designed to work in
conjunction with a component, other modules may be developed
independently of a component.<br />
<div class="section"><p><br />To maintain compatibility with older versions, this tutorial does not cover the use of
